title: The Pony Rider Boys in Texas
creator: Frank Gee Patchin
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Pony Rider Boys in Texas, by Frank Gee Patchin. Yee-hawww! The Pony Rider Boys are on the trail again! In the second book of this series, Professor Zepplin has taken the young men to San Diego, Texas, to experience the life of a cowboy. The cattle drive will take them across the great state of Texas, where they will meet many dangers and adventures. (Summary by Ann Boulais) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
